  "text": "The non-planar numerator ∆ 332 = ∆( ) can, of course, be obtained directly from its cut. However, we can avoid calculating this non-planar cut explicitly by relating it to a planar cut. We do so in two steps: first, we coalesce two (ordered) three-point trees into a limit of an ordered four-point tree; then we use the BCJ relations [CITATION_1] satisfied by the ordered four-point tree to reorder the legs until the complete diagram becomes planar.",
